{"title_page": "Meadow Williams", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Meadow Williams\n| image        =  \n|caption= \n|birth_name = Melanie Kay Williams<ref name=kessler/>\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1966|2|10}}\n| birth_place  = [[Miami]], [[Florida]], U.S.\n| education    =  \n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = 1989\u2013present\n}}\n\n==Life and career==\nWilliams born as Melanie Kay Williams in [[Miami]], [[Florida]] and grew up in [[Tennessee]].<ref name=tvg>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/meadow-williams/bio/257157|title=Meadow Williams &#124; TV Guide|website=TVGuide.com}}</ref> She began performing in high school and later moved to [[New York City]] for working as a model. In New York, Williams studied acting at [[Larry Moss (acting coach)|Larry Moss Studio]]<ref name=tvg/> and later moved to Los Angeles when she began appearing in episodes of television series include ''[[Murder, She Wrote]]'', ''[[Dream On (TV series)|Dream On]]'' and ''[[Married... with Children]]''. Williams also had secondary roles in films ''[[Beverly Hills Cop III]]'' (1994), ''[[The Mask (1994 film)|The Mask]]'' (1994) and ''[[Apollo 13 (film)|Apollo 13]]'' (1995).\n\nIn 2008, Williams began producing and starring in the independent films, include the leading roles in ''Skeletons in the Desert'' (2008), ''Raven'' (2010), and ''[[Mysteria (film)|Mysteria]]'' (2011). She produced and co-starred opposite [[Samantha Morton]] in the 2013 horror film ''[[The Harvest (2013 film)|The Harvest]]'', and well as action film ''[[Den of Thieves (film)|Den of Thieves]]'' (2018) and romantic drama ''[[After (2019 film)|After]]'' (2019).<ref name=dj>{{Cite web|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/entertainment/entertainment/meadow-williams-talks-after-film-motivations-and-acting-advice/article/547364|title=Meadow Williams talks 'After' film, motivations and acting advice (Includes interview)|date=April 10, 2019|website=www.digitaljournal.com}}</ref> In 2017, she won [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Digital Daytime Drama Series]] as a producer of web-series ''[[The Bay (web series)|The Bay]]''.<ref name=dj/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0931291/awards|title=Meadow Williams|website=IMDb}}</ref> She starred opposite [[Sylvester Stallone]] in the 2018 action film ''[[Backtrace (film)|Backtrace]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/backtrace|title=Backtrace (2018)|via=www.rottentomatoes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/backtrace-review-1203089356/|title=Film Review: \u2018Backtrace\u2019|first1=Joe|last1=Leydon|first2=Joe|last2=Leydon|date=December 14, 2018}}</ref> and alongside [[Bruce Willis]] in the 2019 thriller ''[[10 Minutes Gone]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/10-minutes-gone-1243578|title='10 Minutes Gone': Film Review|website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> She next played the role of [[Mildred Gillars]] in the drama film ''[[Axis Sally (film)|Axis Sally]]'' opposite [[Al Pacino]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/al-pacino-axis-sally-nazi-propaganda-voice-sally-gillars-michael-polish-moviepass-films-meadow-williams-1202488517/|title=Al Pacino, Meadow Williams Star In MoviePass Films Drama \u2018Axis Sally\u2019|first1=Mike Fleming|last1=Jr|first2=Mike Fleming|last2=Jr|date=November 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 2002, Williams meet her second husband, Gerald Kessler, a vitamin tycoon multi-millionaire who was 31 years her senior.<ref name=kessler>{{Cite web|url=https://truecrimedaily.com/2015/11/16/tycoon-leaves-800m-to-young-widow-but-is-she-a-bigamist/|title=Tycoon leaves $800M to young widow - but is she a bigamist? &#124; Truecrimedaily.com|website=crimewatch}}</ref> In 2010, Kessler finally divorced his wife of 55 years, Betty Kessler and married to Williams. Kessler died in 2015 and signing over almost all of his $800 million estate to Williams.<ref name=kessler/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/actress-obtained-husband-800m-estate-fraud-suit-article-1.2360524|title=Actress obtained late husband\u2019s $800M estate through fraud: lawsuit|first=Ginger Adams|last=Otis|website=nydailynews.com}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''The Nutzoids at Cannibal Cove''\n| Bitsy\n|  \n|-\n|1994\n|''Turn of the Blade''\n|Calendar Girl\n|\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Beverly Hills Cop III]]''\n|Spider Rider\n|\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[The Mask (1994 film)|The Mask]]''\n|Pebbles\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Apollo 13 (film)|Apollo 13]]''\n|Kim\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Virtual Seduction]]''\n|Hostess\n|Television film\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[The Extreme Adventures of Super Dave]]''\n|Girl Driver\n|\n|-\n|2001\n|''[[Soulkeeper]]''\n|Buxom Babe\n|\n|-\n|2003\n|''[[The Box (2003 film)|The Box]]''\n|Dancer\n|\n|-\n|2004\n|''Uh Oh!''\n|Tara\n|\n|-\n|2004\n|''[[Miss Cast Away and the Island Girls|Miss Cast Away]]''\n|Flight Attendant\n|Television film\n|-\n|2008\n|''Jack Rio''\n|Andrea Shane\n|Also producer\n|-\n|2008\n|''Skeletons in the Desert''\n|Casey Stevens\n|Also producer\n|-\n|2010\n|''Light Years Away''\n|Misty\n|\n|-\n|2010\n|''Raven''\n|Raven\n|Also producer\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[Mysteria (film)|Mysteria]]''\n|Lavinia\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|''Sebastian''\n|Miranda Barnes\n|\n|-\n|2013\n|''[[The Harvest (2013 film)|The Harvest]]''\n|Sandra\n|Also producer\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Reclaim (film)|Reclaim]]''\n|Barmaid \n|\n|-\n|2014\n|''[[Reach Me]]''\n|Phyllis\n|\n|-\n|2016\n|''[[Officer Downe (film)|Officer Downe]]''\n|Mother Supreme\n|\n|-\n|2017\n|''The Intruders''\n|Lily\n|Also producer and writer \n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Den of Thieves (film)|Den of Thieves]]''\n|Holly\n|Also executive producer\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Backtrace (film)|Backtrace]]''\n|Erin\n|Also executive producer\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[After (2019 film)|After]]''\n|Professor Soto\n|Also producer\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[10 Minutes Gone]]''\n|Claire\n|Also executive producer\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[Escape Plan: The Extractors]]''\n|\n|Executive producer\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Boss Level]]''\n|Pam\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|''Broken Soldier''\n|Mrs. Ancilla\n|\n|-\n|2020\n|''[[Axis Sally (film)|Axis Sally]] ''\n|[[Mildred Gillars]]\n|Also executive producer\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0931291}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century American actresses]]\n[[Category:American film actresses]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Miami]]\n[[Category:American film producers]]\n[[Category:American women film producers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Meadow Williams\n| image        =  \n|caption= \n|birth_name = Melanie Kay Williams<ref name=kessler/>\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1966|2|10}}\n| birth_place  = [[Miami]], [[Florida]], U.S.\n| education    =  \n| occupation   = Actress\n| years_active = 1989\u2013present\n}}\n\n==Life and career==\nWilliams born as Melanie Kay Williams in [[Miami]], [[Florida]] and grew up in [[Tennessee]].<ref name=tvg>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/meadow-williams/bio/257157|title=Meadow Williams &#124; TV Guide|website=TVGuide.com}}</ref> She began performing in high school and later moved to [[New York City]] for working as a model. In New York, Williams studied acting at [[Larry Moss (acting coach)|Larry Moss Studio]]<ref name=tvg/> and later moved to Los Angeles when she began appearing in episodes of television series include ''[[Murder, She Wrote]]'', ''[[Dream On (TV series)|Dream On]]'' and ''[[Married... with Children]]''. Williams also had secondary roles in films ''[[Beverly Hills Cop III]]'' (1994), ''[[The Mask (1994 film)|The Mask]]'' (1994) and ''[[Apollo 13 (film)|Apollo 13]]'' (1995).\n\nIn 2008, Williams began producing and starring in the independent films, include the leading roles in ''Skeletons in the Desert'' (2008), ''Raven'' (2010), and ''[[Mysteria (film)|Mysteria]]'' (2011). She produced and co-starred opposite [[Samantha Morton]] in the 2013 horror film ''[[The Harvest (2013 film)|The Harvest]]'', and well as action film ''[[Den of Thieves (film)|Den of Thieves]]'' (2018) and romantic drama ''[[After (2019 film)|After]]'' (2019).<ref name=dj>{{Cite web|url=http://www.digitaljournal.com/entertainment/entertainment/meadow-williams-talks-after-film-motivations-and-acting-advice/article/547364|title=Meadow Williams talks 'After' film, motivations and acting advice (Includes interview)|date=April 10, 2019|website=www.digitaljournal.com}}</ref> In 2017, she won [[Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Digital Daytime Drama Series]] as a producer of web-series ''[[The Bay (web series)|The Bay]]''.<ref name=dj/><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0931291/awards|title=Meadow Williams|website=IMDb}}</ref> She starred opposite [[Sylvester Stallone]] in the 2018 action film ''[[Backtrace (film)|Backtrace]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/backtrace|title=Backtrace (2018)|via=www.rottentomatoes.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://variety.com/2018/film/news/backtrace-review-1203089356/|title=Film Review: \u2018Backtrace\u2019|first1=Joe|last1=Leydon|first2=Joe|last2=Leydon|date=December 14, 2018}}</ref> and alongside [[Bruce Willis]] in the 2019 thriller ''[[10 Minutes Gone]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/10-minutes-gone-1243578|title='10 Minutes Gone': Film Review|website=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> She next played the role of [[Mildred Gillars]] in the drama film ''[[Axis Sally (film)|Axis Sally]]'' opposite [[Al Pacino]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://deadline.com/2018/11/al-pacino-axis-sally-nazi-propaganda-voice-sally-gillars-michael-polish-moviepass-films-meadow-williams-1202488517/|title=Al Pacino, Meadow Williams Star In MoviePass Films Drama \u2018Axis Sally\u2019|first1=Mike Fleming|last1=Jr|first2=Mike Fleming|last2=Jr|date=November 1, 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 2002, Williams meet her second husband, Gerald Kessler, a vitamin tycoon multi-millionaire who was 31 years her senior.<ref name=kessler>{{Cite web|url=https://truecrimedaily.com/2015/11/16/tycoon-leaves-800m-to-young-widow-but-is-she-a-bigamist/|title=Tycoon leaves $800M to young widow - but is she a bigamist? &#124; Truecrimedaily.com|website=crimewatch}}</ref> In 2010, Kessler finally divorced his wife of 55 years, Betty Kessler and married to Williams. Kessler died in 2015 and signing over almost all of his $800 million estate to Williams.<ref name=kessler/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/actress-obtained-husband-800m-estate-fraud-suit-article-1.2360524|title=Actress obtained late husband\u2019s $800M estate through fraud: lawsuit|first=Ginger Adams|last=Otis|website=nydailynews.com}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1989\n| ''The Nutzoids at Cannibal Cove''\n| Bitsy\n|  \n|-\n|1994\n|''Turn of the Blade''\n|Calendar Girl\n|\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Beverly Hills Cop III]]''\n|Spider Rider\n|\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[The Mask (1994 film)|The Mask]]''\n|Pebbles\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Apollo 13 (film)|Apollo 13]]''\n|Kim\n|\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[Virtual Seduction]]''\n|Hostess\n|Television film\n|-\n|2000\n|''[[The Extreme Adventures of Super Dave]]''\n|Girl Driver\n|\n|-\n|2001\n|''[[Soulkeeper]]''\n|Buxom Babe\n|\n|-\n|2003\n|''[[The Box (2003 film)|The Box]]''\n|Dancer\n|\n|-\n|2004\n|''Uh Oh!''\n|Tara\n|\n|-\n|2004\n|''[[Miss Cast Away and the Island Girls|Miss Cast Away]]''\n|Flight Attendant\n|Television film\n|-\n|2008\n|''Jack Rio''\n|Andrea Shane\n|Also producer\n|-\n|2008\n|''Skeletons in the Desert''\n|Casey Stevens\n|Also producer\n|-\n|2010\n|''Light Years Away''\n|Misty\n|\n|-\