              = \n| starring                 = {{ubl|[[Vivek Oberoi]]|[[Richa Chadha]]|[[Tanuj Virwani]]|[[Siddhant Chaturvedi]]|[[Angad Bedi]]|[[Aamir Bashir]]|[[Sapna Pabbi]]}}\n| composer                 = \n| country                  = India\n| language                 = {{ubl|Hindi|English}}\n| num_seasons              = 2\n| num_episodes             = 20\n| list_episodes            = #Episodes\n| executive_producer       = {{ubl|[[Ritesh Sidhwani]]|[[Farhan Akhtar]]}}<ref name=\"ExpressReview\"/>\n| camera                   = [[Single-camera setup|Single-camera]]\n| runtime                  = 40\u201347 minutes\n| company                  = [[Excel Entertainment]]\n| distributor              = \n| network                  = [[Amazon Video]]\n| first_run                = \n| released                 = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|7|10}}<ref name=\"ExpressReview\"/>\n| last_aired               = present\n| writer                   = {{Plainlist|\n* Karan Anshuman\n* Saurav Dey\n* Ameya Sarda\n* Niren Bhatt\n* Sailesh Ramaswamy\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Inside Edge''''' is an Indian [[web television]] series based on a fictional [[Twenty20|T20]] cricket team, ''Mumbai Mavericks'' that plays in the Power-Play League (based on [[Indian Premier League]]).<ref name=\"ExpressReview\" /><ref name=\"TodayReview\" /> It premiered on [[Amazon Video]] on 10 July 2017. This is [[Amazon Prime Video]]\u2019s first Indian [[List of original programs distributed by Amazon|original series]].<ref name=\"ExpressReview\" /><ref name=\"firstamazon\">{{Cite web | title = Amazon web series \u2018Inside Edge\u2019 turns the murky side of Indian cricket inside out | last = Ghosh | first = Devarsi | work = Scroll.in | date =  | accessdate = 11 July 2017 | url = https://thereel.scroll.in/843228/amazon-web-series-inside-edge-turns-the-murky-side-of-indian-cricket-inside-out | quote = Amazon Prime Video\u2019s first original Indian web series }}</ref> The series stars [[Vivek Oberoi]], [[Richa Chada]], [[Siddhant Chaturvedi]], [[Tanuj Virwani]] and [[Angad Bedi]].<ref name=\"dnaBedi\">{{Cite web | title = Angad Bedi reveals he got inspired from MS Dhoni for his role in 'Inside Edge' |work = [[Daily News and Analysis]] | date =14 July 2017 | accessdate = 17 July 2017 | url = http://www.dnaindia.com/bollywood/report-angad-bedi-reveals-he-got-inspired-from-ms-dhoni-for-his-role-in-inside-edge-2502363 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | title = Amazon Prime starts its Indian innings with an aggressively mediocre show, Inside Edge | first=Raja |last=Sen |work = [[Live Mint]] | date =13 July 2017  | accessdate = 17 July 2017 | url = http://www.livemint.com/Leisure/62edpOiMTeU5fGoNAThIMO/Amazon-starts-its-Indian-innings-with-an-aggressively-medioc.html }}</ref><ref name=\"Virwanifreepress\">{{Cite web | title = Tanuj Virvani: Tashan on the edge | first=Nikita |last=Wadhawan |work = [[The Free Press Journal]] | date =10 July 2017  | accessdate = 17 July 2017 | url = http://www.freepressjournal.in/entertainment/tanuj-virvani-tashan-on-the-edge/1099959 }}</ref>  The first season premiered in July 2017.<ref name=\"ExpressReview\" /><ref name=\"Chada\">{{Cite web | title = Hope someone casts Richa Chadha with me in a film: Angad Bedi |work = [[Hindustan Times]] | date =15 July 2017 | accessdate = 17 July 2017 | first=Sweta | last=Kaushal| url = http://www.hindustantimes.com/bollywood/hope-someone-casts-richa-chadha-with-me-in-a-film-angad-bedi/story-AR42rK10E5ns8lDVYcOlbO.html }}</ref> The series has been positively received by critics and audience and nominated for Best Drama series at [[46th International Emmy Awards]].<ref name=\"audience\" /><ref name=\"FirstpostReview\" /> The second season of the series premiered on December 6, 2019 worldwide.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://gadgets.ndtv.com/entertainment/features/inside-edge-2-cast-season-2-season-1-review-web-series-imdb-2-release-date-trailer-poster-director-2140888|title=All You Need to Know About Inside Edge Season 2|website=NDTV Gadgets 360|language=en|access-date=2019-12-13}}</ref> Amazon Prime Originals recently announce that Inside Edge Web Series is back with season 3.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.uslis.com/2020/04/inside-edge-season-3-web-series-movie.html|title=Inside Edge Season 3, Web Series movie Trailer, Release Date, Cast, Episodes \u2013 Amazon Prime|access-date=2020-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nInside Edge is the story of the Mumbai Mavericks, a T20 cricket franchise playing in the Powerplay League. Set in a landscape of conflicting interests, where selfishness is almost a virtue, where money and power go hand in hand, the series traces the ups and downs in the Powerplay league as the Mumbai Mavericks face ownership problems along with accusations of match fixing.<ref name=\"holl_Amaz\">{{Cite web | title = Amazon Unveils First Indian Original Series 'Inside Edge' | author = | work = [[The Hollywood Reporter]] | date =8 June 2017 | accessdate = 10 July 2017 | url = http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/amazon-unveils-first-indian-original-series-inside-edge-1011420 }}</ref>\n\n==Cast==\n===Main===\n* [[Vivek Oberoi]] as Vikrant Dhawan,<ref name=\"FirstpostReview\"/> The owner of one of the world's leading sports management companies\n* [[Aamir Bashir]] as Bhaisahab/Yashvardhan Patil President of Indian Cricket Board and the founder of The Power Play League. (Season 2)\n* [[Richa Chadda]] as Zarina Malik,<ref name=Chada/> A fading actress and co-owner of the Mumbai Mavericks.\n* [[Sapna Pabbi]] as Mantra Patil, <ref name=\"FirstpostReview\"/> Co-Owner of Mumbai Mavericks (Season 2), Daughter of Bhaisahab and Vayu's Girlfriend.\n* [[Tanuj Virwani]] as Vayu Raghavan,<ref name=Virwanifreepress/> The star player of the Mavericks and a moody [[wikt:hothead|hothead]], captain of Mumbai Mavericks (Season 2) and Mantra's Boyfriend.\n* [[Siddhant Chaturvedi]] as Prashant Kanaujia,<ref name=\"FirstpostReview\" />  A [[rookie]] fast bowler from [[Mirzapur]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] hinterland who joins the Mavericks\n* [[Angad Bedi]] as Arvind Vashishth,<ref name=dnaBedi/> an ex -Indian international player and the captain of the Mavericks (Season 1) and captain of the Haryana Hurricanes (Season 2)\n* [[Amit Sial]] as  Devender Mishra, Maverick's spinner in Season 1 then Hurricane's spinner in Season 2\n* [[Sayani Gupta]] as Rohini Raghavan,<ref name=\"FirstpostReview\"/> sister of Vayu and the Chief Team Analyst of the Mavericks and then the Hurricanes.\n* [[Sanjay Suri]] as Niranjan Suri,<ref name=\"FirstpostReview\"/> The coach of the Mavericks in Season 1 (Season 1)\n* [[Sarah-Jane Dias]] as Meera Nagpal,<ref name=\"FirstpostReview\"/> a journalist and ex-girlfriend of Vayu (Season 1)\n* Jitin Gulati as Pritish Chakravarty, Vikrant's right-hand man (recurring, Season 1) , BhaiSahab's Right Hand man (Season 2)\n* [[Manu Rishi]] as Manoharlal Handa, a rich but eccentric businessman and the owner of rival team Haryana Hurricanes (recurring, Season 1; Main, Season 2)\n* [[Elli Avram]] as Sandy, Cheerleader of Mumbai Mavericks and Girlfriend of Prashant (Season 2)\n\n===Recurring===\n* [[Karan Oberoi]] as Imtiaz Khan, an actor and Zarina's ex-boyfriend\n* Gaurav Sharma as  Moses Alexander, the coach of the Mavericks (Season 2; guest, Season 1)\n* [[Asha Saini]] as Ayesha Dewan, Handa's partner and a power broker based in Delhi and owner of Bangalore Blitz\n* [[Vidya Malvade]] as Tisha Chopra,<ref name=dnaBedi/> an ex -Indian international player and the bowling coach of the Haryana Hurricanes (Season 2)\n* Nitanshi Goel as Young Rohini Raghavan\n* [[Alexx O'Nell]] as Craig Litner, Vice-Captain of the Mavericks (Season 1)\n* Manuj Sharma as KR Raghunath, Maverick's wicket-keeper (Season 1)\n* Edward Sonnenblick as Hamish Mccall, Maverick's fast bowler (Season 1)\n* Ogunro Gbolabo Lucas as Dwight Johnson, Maverick\u2019s fast bowler\n* [[Aahana Kumra]] as Shahana Vashishth, Arvind's estranged wife (Season 1)\n* Himanshi Choudhry as Sudha Dhawan, Vikrant's wife\n* Akashdeep Arora as Tanay, a team Analyst of the Mavericks\n* Mahnaz Damania as Raghunath's girlfriend (Season 1)\n* Zachary Coffin as Haryana Hurricanes Captain Jack Woolley (Season 1)\n* [[Luke Kenny]] as GDPA official Wolfgang Hummels (Season 2)\n* Alekh Sangal as news anchor Girish Mukherjee (Season 2)\n\n==Reception==\nThe series has received critical acclaim for performance and storyline. The acting performance of [[Siddhant Chaturvedi]], Vivek Oberoi, Tanuj Virvani, Richa Chadha, Sayani Gupta and Angad Bedi has been especially praised.<ref name=\"FirstpostReview\">{{Cite web | title = Inside Edge episode 1 review: This gripping web series on big bad cricket world needs better villain | work = [[Firstpost]] | date =12 July 2017  | first=Devansh | last=Sharma | accessdate = 17 July 2017 | url = http://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/inside-edge-episode-1-review-this-gripping-web-series-on-big-bad-cricket-world-needs-better-villain-3789253.html }}</ref><ref name=audience>{{Cite web | title = Inside Edge Receives Massive Response; Audience Demands For A Season 2 | work = Businessofcinema | date =13 July 2017  | accessdate = 17 July 2017 | url = https://businessofcinema.com/bollywood_news/inside-edge-receives-massive-response-audience-demands-season-2/405571 }}</ref> [[India Today]] called the series ''\"perfectly cast and technically first rate\"''.<ref name=\"TodayReview\">{{Cite web | title = Inside Edge, the Amazon India TV series, gets a rousing start | last = Krishna | first = Sankaran | work = [[India Today]] | date =14 July 2017  | accessdate = 17 July 2017 | url = http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/vivek-oberoi-web-series-amazon-india-cricket-richa-chadha/1/1001959.html }}</ref> [[The Indian Express]] praised the performance of all actors saying that ''\"web-series packs interesting punch shouldered by some honest performances\"''  and also stated that the shows quality hasn't been compromised just because web series is a far smaller medium than films.<ref name=\"ExpressReview\">{{Cite web | title = Inside Edge: Farhan Akhtar-produced web-series packs interesting punch shouldered by some honest performances | work = [[The Indian Express]] | date =11 July 2017  | accessdate = 17 July 2017 | url = http://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/inside-edge-review-episode-1-farhan-akhtar-vivek-oberoi-richa-chadha-sayani-gupta-sanjay-suri-web-series-4745133/ }}</ref> [[Firstpost]] positively reviewed the series saying ''\"The characters are so seamlessly integrated into the narrative that it does not feel like a make believe world\"''.<ref name=\"FirstpostReview\"/>\n}}\n\n==Season 1==\n\n===Episodes===\n{{Episode table |background=#0257AC |overall=  |title= |writer= |director=[[Karan Anshuman]] |airdate=10 July 2017 |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 1\n |Title = Powerplay1\n |DirectedBy = Karan Anshuman\n |WrittenBy = Karan Anshuman\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|7|10}}\n |ShortSummary = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be removed or reverted. Superficially modifying copyrighted content or closely paraphrasing it, even if the source is cited, still constitutes a copyright violation. Summaries should be about 100 to 200 words in length, per WP:TVPLOT, and those substantially less than 100 words are most likely to be scrutinized for possible copyright violation. -->\n |LineColor = 0257AC\n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber = 2\n |Title = Bunny\n |DirectedBy = Karan Anshuman\n |WrittenBy = Ameya Sarda\n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|7|10}}\n |ShortSummary = <!-- Episode summaries must be expressed in your own words. Do NOT submit content you find from another web site as it is plagiarism and likely a copyright violation, which Wikipedia cannot accept and will be remo